00:11:26,261 --> 00:11:27,381
But they were really high up.

197
00:11:27,421 --> 00:11:29,102
And you were having to fight these battles with these

198
00:11:29,122 --> 00:11:30,842
drones really high above you.

199
00:11:30,862 --> 00:11:32,003
And I'm like, well, that's great.

200
00:11:32,123 --> 00:11:34,523
But it's really not that much fun, because

201
00:11:34,543 --> 00:11:35,364
they're so far away.

202
00:11:35,664 --> 00:11:38,185
And it's not as much fun to be looking directly up at them.

203
00:11:38,605 --> 00:11:42,367
So what we ended up doing was taking the volume in which they could fly and just bringing it down

204
00:11:42,767 --> 00:11:45,808
to the point where the drones will actually buzz the player by their head.

205
00:11:45,928 --> 00:11:50,030
And there's a lot of people now who just, I don't know, we've seen a lot of posts of people breaking their lamps

206
00:11:50,090 --> 00:11:54,852
or ceiling fans of various things, in particular when they're playing Saija and using her sword,

207
00:11:54,932 --> 00:11:57,414
specifically the drone buzzing by and whacking it out of the air.

208
00:11:57,434 --> 00:11:59,995
And they couldn't do that if the drones were really high up.

209
00:12:00,055 --> 00:12:05,918
So again, that's another example where the closer we bring the action to the player, just the more immersive it is.

210
00:12:09,663 --> 00:12:11,056
Okay, next slide.

211
00:12:12,283 --> 00:12:16,884
So here we also want to talk about not only are we pursuing

